{% comment %} Science & Evidence — inline section {% endcomment %}

<div class="scm-wrap">
  <div class="scm-inner">

    <div class="scm-header">
      <h2 class="scm-title">The Science</h2>
      <p class="scm-intro">Clinical-grade sensors. Peer-reviewed methods. Here's what powers the ring.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="scm-grid">

      <div class="scm-stat">
        <p class="scm-number">PPG</p>
        <p class="scm-label">Photoplethysmography</p>
        <p class="scm-desc">Optical heart-rate sensor measures blood volume pulse at 100+ Hz — the same principle used in hospital pulse oximeters.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="scm-stat">
        <p class="scm-number">SpO₂</p>
        <p class="scm-label">Blood oxygen saturation</p>
        <p class="scm-desc">Red and infrared LEDs detect haemoglobin absorption to estimate blood-oxygen levels during sleep.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="scm-stat">
        <p class="scm-number">6-axis</p>
        <p class="scm-label">Motion & activity</p>
        <p class="scm-desc">Accelerometer + gyroscope track movement patterns to separate restless sleep from true wakefulness.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="scm-stat">
        <p class="scm-number">0.1 °C</p>
        <p class="scm-label">Skin temperature</p>
        <p class="scm-desc">Precision NTC sensor detects nightly temperature variation — an early biomarker for recovery and illness onset.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="scm-quote">
      <svg class="scm-quote-mark" viewBox="0 0 40 32" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M0 32V19.2C0 8.533 5.867 2.133 17.6 0l1.6 3.2C13.067 4.8 10.133 8 9.6 12.8H16V32H0zm22.4 0V19.2C22.4 8.533 28.267 2.133 40 0l1.6 3.2C35.467 4.8 32.533 8 32 12.8H38.4V32H22.4z" fill="#8B5CC0" opacity="0.18"/>
      </svg>
      <p class="scm-quote-text">Smart rings may be more accurate for sleep tracking than smartwatches — and their finger-based sensors offer better signal quality than wrist-worn devices.</p>
      <p class="scm-quote-attr">Harvard Health Publishing · Harvard Medical School</p>
    </div>

    <div class="scm-sources">
      <p class="scm-sources-label">Endorsed by</p>
      <div class="scm-sources-row">
        <div class="scm-badge">
          <p class="scm-badge-name">Harvard Health Publishing</p>
          <p class="scm-badge-sub">Harvard Medical School</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scm-badge">
          <p class="scm-badge-name">Sleep Foundation</p>
          <p class="scm-badge-sub">Evidence-based sleep research</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scm-badge">
          <p class="scm-badge-name">JMIR mHealth</p>
          <p class="scm-badge-sub">Peer-reviewed wearable studies</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .scm-wrap {
    background: #FAF8FF;
    padding: 72px 20px;
  }

  .scm-inner {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .scm-header {
    text-align: center !important;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .scm-eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B5CC0;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  .scm-title {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1A0826;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .scm-intro {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #5A3A9A;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    text-align: center !important;
  }

  .scm-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: rgba(107,63,160,0.12);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .scm-stat {
    background: #F0E8FF;
    padding: 28px 24px;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .scm-stat:hover { background: #E4D0FF; }

  .scm-number {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 4vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    color: #4A2980;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .scm-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B5CC0;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }

  .scm-desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: #5A3A9A;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .scm-quote {
    position: relative;
    padding: 28px 24px 24px;
    background: #F0E8FF;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(107,63,160,0.15);
    border-left: 3px solid #8B5CC0;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .scm-quote-mark {
    position: absolute;
    top: 16px; right: 20px;
    width: 28px; height: 22px;
  }

  .scm-quote-text {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #1A0826;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .scm-quote-attr {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #8B5CC0;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .scm-sources-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B5CC0;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    text-align: center;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .scm-sources-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .scm-badge {
    background: #F0E8FF;
    border: 1px solid rgba(107,63,160,0.18);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    text-align: center;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 180px;
  }

  .scm-badge-name {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1A0826;
    margin: 0 0 3px;
  }

  .scm-badge-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: #5A3A9A;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .scm-wrap { padding: 48px 20px; }
    .scm-sources-row { flex-direction: column; }
    .scm-badge { min-width: unset; }
  }
</style>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "The Science",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "section-science-modal",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
